Circlizing_Example

1 a simple example

## setup data
m <- matrix(c(11975,  5871, 8916, 2868,
              1951, 10048, 2060, 6171,
              8010, 16145, 8090, 8045,
              1013,   990,  940, 6907),
            byrow = TRUE,
            nrow = 4, ncol = 4)

library("circlize")
chordDiagram(m)

3 plot multiple diagrams

par(mar=rep(0,4), bg = "black")

layout(matrix(1:9, 3, 3))
for(i in 1:9) {
  factors = 1:8
  par(mar = c(0.5, 0.5, 0.5, 0.5))
  circos.par(cell.padding = c(0, 0, 0, 0))
  circos.initialize(factors, xlim = c(0, 1))
  circos.trackPlotRegion(ylim = c(0, 1), track.height = 0.05,
                         bg.col = rand_color(8), bg.border = NA)
  for(i in 1:20) {
    se = sample(1:8, 2)
    circos.link(se[1], runif(2), se[2], runif(2),
                col = rand_color(1, transparency = 0.4))
  }
  circos.clear()
}
